This simplifies to `k - 1 < n * δ * k / (b - a)`. This inequality is likely true given `hfine : 2 * (b - a) / n < δ`, which implies `n > 2 * (b - a) / δ`.

Therefore, `|x_{j,l} - y_j| < δ`, so by `hunif`, `|f(x_{j,l}) - f(y_j)| < ε`.

Now, the difference between the sums can be bounded by:
`|S_{n*k} - S_n| = | (b - a) / n * ∑_{j=0}^{n-1} [ (1/k) * ∑_{l=0}^{k-1} f(x_{j,l}) - f(y_j) ] |`
`≤ (b - a) / n * ∑_{j=0}^{n-1} [ (1/k) * ∑_{l=0}^{k-1} |f(x_{j,l}) - f(y_j)| ]`
`≤ (b - a) / n * ∑_{j=0}^{n-1} [ (1/k) * ∑_{l=0}^{k-1} ε ]`
`= (b - a) / n * ∑_{j=0}^{n-1} [ (1/k) * k * ε ]`
`= (b - a) / n * ∑_{j=0}^{n-1} ε`
`= (b - a) / n * n * ε`
`= (b - a) * ε`

This is exactly the bound we need.

